org.openimaj.image.processing.transform

Class PiecewiseMeshWarp<T,I extends Image<T,I>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.image.processing.transform.PiecewiseMeshWarp<T,I>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the pixel type
    I - the actual image of the concrete subclass
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ImageProcessor<I>, Processor<I>

    public class PiecewiseMeshWarp<T,I extends Image<T,I>>
extends Object
implements ImageProcessor<I>
    Implementation of a piecewise warp. The warp can be piecewise affine, piecewise homographic or a mixture of the two. Basically this means you can warp images represented by triangles, quads or a mixture of the two.
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
